  "body": "- [x ] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nRunning the most trivial truff truffle command like `truffle version` seems to take in excess of 2.5 seconds. Is that acceptable? Is there a way to speed what appears to be simple nodejs loading? \r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n* Install truffle 4.1.13 (e.g. `npm install -g truffle`)\r\n* install truffle 5.0.0-beta (I did locally in a directory)\r\n\r\nThen \r\n\r\n```\r\n$ time /usr/bin/truffle version\r\nTruffle v4.1.13 (core: 4.1.13)\r\nSolidity v0.4.24 (solc-js)\r\n\r\nreal\t0m1.531s\r\nuser\t0m1.243s\r\nsys\t0m0.100s\r\n\r\n$ time node ./node_modules/.bin/truffle version\r\nTruffle v5.0.0-beta.1 (core: 5.0.0-beta.1)\r\nSolidity v0.4.25 (solc-js)\r\n\r\nreal\t0m2.819s\r\nuser\t0m2.585s\r\nsys\t0m0.262s\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nAbout 1 second response time to show the version\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nSee above. \"user\" time between 4.1.13 and 5.0.0-beta1 doubled. Elapsed almost doubled.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Ubuntu bionic\r\n* Ethereum client:\r\n* Truffle version 4.1.13 and 5.0.0-beta1\r\n* node version: v8.10.0\r\n* npm version: 3.5.2\r\n",
